<p>The concept of five pillars is taken from the <a href="/wiki/Hadith" title="Hadith">Hadith</a> collections, notably those of <a href="/wiki/Sahih_Al-Bukhari" title="Sahih Al-Bukhari" class="mw-redirect">Sahih Al-Bukhari</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sahih_Muslim" title="Sahih Muslim">Sahih Muslim</a>. The Qur'an reveals the “five pillars” of Islam, the five ritual expressions that define orthodox Muslim religious belief and practice. Wudu is a washing in Salah and it is the first thing they do for Salah.</p>
